<div id="calcOverlay" onclick="if(event.target===this)closeCalc()"><div id="calcPanel">
<div class="chdr"><div><div class="cttl">⚡ VFD Unit Converter</div><div class="csub">Formulas: Rockwell Publications 20A-UM001P-EN-P &amp; 520-UM001O-EN-E</div></div><button class="ccls" onclick="closeCalc()">✕</button></div>
<div class="cbody">
<div class="csec"><div class="cshdr" onclick="tCS('s1')"><span>🔄</span><span class="csttl">RPM ↔ Hertz</span><span class="csfml">Hz = RPM ÷ 60</span><span class="cstog" id="s1t">▲</span></div>
<div class="csbody" id="s1b">
<div class="cnote">1 revolution/second = 1 Hz; 1 minute = 60 seconds.</div><hr class="chr">
<div class="crow"><label>RPM →</label><input class="cin" id="r2h" type="number" min="0" placeholder="e.g. 1750" oninput="cRH()"><span class="cu">RPM</span><span class="ca">→</span><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="r2ho">—</span><span class="cru">Hz</span></div></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Hz →</label><input class="cin" id="h2r" type="number" min="0" placeholder="e.g. 60" oninput="cHR()"><span class="cu">Hz</span><span class="ca">→</span><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="h2ro">—</span><span class="cru">RPM</span></div></div>
</div></div>
<div class="csec"><div class="cshdr" onclick="tCS('s2')"><span>⚙️</span><span class="csttl">Motor Speed → Drive Frequency (with Poles)</span><span class="csfml">Hz = (RPM × Poles) ÷ 120</span><span class="cstog" id="s2t">▲</span></div>
<div class="csbody" id="s2b">
<div class="cnote">Frequency a VFD must output to run a motor at a given shaft speed. Formula behind PF70 P043/P044/P049. [Source: 20A-UM001P-EN-P P049]</div><hr class="chr">
<div class="crow"><label>Shaft speed</label><input class="cin" id="mrpm" type="number" min="0" placeholder="e.g. 1750" oninput="cMH()"><span class="cu">RPM</span></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Motor poles</label><input class="cin" id="mpol" type="number" min="2" max="40" step="2" placeholder="e.g. 4" oninput="cMH()"><span class="cu">poles</span></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Drive output →</label><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="mhzo">—</span><span class="cru">Hz</span></div></div>
<hr class="chr">
<div class="cnote">Calculate poles: "Poles = (120 × Motor NP Hertz) ÷ Motor NP RPM" [20A-UM001P-EN-P P049]</div>
<div class="crow"><label>Nameplate Hz</label><input class="cin" id="nphz" type="number" min="0" placeholder="e.g. 60" oninput="cPL()"><span class="cu">Hz</span></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Nameplate RPM</label><input class="cin" id="nprpm" type="number" min="0" placeholder="e.g. 1750" oninput="cPL()"><span class="cu">RPM</span></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Pole count →</label><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="polo">—</span><span class="cru">poles</span></div></div>
</div></div>
<div class="csec"><div class="cshdr" onclick="tCS('s3')"><span>📊</span><span class="csttl">Frequency → Percent of Maximum</span><span class="csfml">% = (Hz ÷ Max Freq) × 100</span><span class="cstog" id="s3t">▲</span></div>
<div class="csbody" id="s3b">
<div class="cnote">For PF70 P091/P092 [Speed Ref Hi/Lo] (Hz) → PF525 P092/P091 [Anlg In 0-10V Hi/Lo] (%). Enter PF525 P44 [Maximum Freq] as divisor. [520-UM001O-EN-E p.99]</div><hr class="chr">
<div class="crow"><label>Frequency</label><input class="cin" id="h2ph" type="number" min="0" placeholder="e.g. 45" oninput="cHP()"><span class="cu">Hz</span></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Maximum Freq</label><input class="cin" id="h2pm" type="number" min="0" placeholder="e.g. 60" oninput="cHP()"><span class="cu">Hz</span></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Result →</label><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="h2po">—</span><span class="cru">%</span></div></div>
</div></div>
<div class="csec"><div class="cshdr" onclick="tCS('s4')"><span>🔌</span><span class="csttl">Voltage → Percent (0–10V Analog)</span><span class="csfml">% = (V ÷ 10) × 100</span><span class="cstog" id="s4t">▲</span></div>
<div class="csbody" id="s4b">
<div class="cnote">PF70 P322/P323/P343/P344/P180/P182 are in Volts. PF525 P089/P091/P092/P101/P103 use percent. 10V = 100%, 5V = 50%, 0V = 0%. [20A-UM001P-EN-P p.63–67, 520-UM001O-EN-E p.98–101]</div><hr class="chr">
<div class="crow"><label>Voltage →</label><input class="cin" id="v2p" type="number" min="0" max="10" step="0.001" placeholder="e.g. 7.5" oninput="cVP()"><span class="cu">V</span><span class="ca">→</span><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="v2po">—</span><span class="cru">%</span></div></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Percent →</label><input class="cin" id="p2v" type="number" min="0" max="100" step="0.1" placeholder="e.g. 75" oninput="cPV()"><span class="cu">%</span><span class="ca">→</span><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="p2vo">—</span><span class="cru">V</span></div></div>
</div></div>
<div class="csec"><div class="cshdr" onclick="tCS('s5')"><span>〰️</span><span class="csttl">milliamps → Percent (4–20 mA)</span><span class="csfml">% = ((mA − 4) ÷ 16) × 100</span><span class="cstog" id="s5t">▲</span></div>
<div class="csbody" id="s5b">
<div class="cnote">PF70 P325/P326 (mA) → PF525 P095/P096 (%). 4mA=0%, 20mA=100%, 12mA=50%. ⚠ Jumper J4 on PF525 must be set to 4-20mA. [20A-UM001P-EN-P p.63, 520-UM001O-EN-E p.100]</div><hr class="chr">
<div class="crow"><label>mA →</label><input class="cin" id="m2p" type="number" min="0" max="20" step="0.001" placeholder="e.g. 12" oninput="cMP()"><span class="cu">mA</span><span class="ca">→</span><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="m2po">—</span><span class="cru">%</span></div></div>
<div class="crow"><label>Percent →</label><input class="cin" id="p2m" type="number" min="0" max="100" step="0.1" placeholder="e.g. 50" oninput="cPM()"><span class="cu">%</span><span class="ca">→</span><div class="cr"><span class="crv" id="p2mo">—</span><span class="cru">mA</span></div></div>
</div></div>
</div></div></div>
